    <P xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" paraDef="topic_title" id="#unique_1">Windows
        installation</P>

    <P paraDef="body">This section includes information on system requirements and installation for
        the desktop version.</P>
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <!--topic/title parent task count=1 outputclass=-->
    <!--STARTSECTION $outputclass=[]-->
    <P xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" paraDef="topic_title1" id="#unique_2">Installing
        Desktop</P>
    <!--mm:mapToParagraphs context ctx = context-->
    <P paraDef="context">Double-click on the pNNNsetup.exe to install MiramoPDF. When prompted,
        navigate to your chosen installation folder (default is <!--SW-D FOUND--><Font
            xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="filepath">C:\Program
            Files\Miramo\</Font><!--SW-D FOUND--><Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            fontDef="filepath"> and click on OK to continue.</Font>
    </P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">If an earlier version of is already installed, you will be
        prompted as shown below:<AFrame xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" wrap="Y"
            position="below" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="start"><Image
                file="screenshots/windows-uninstall-previous.png" width="80mm" keepAspectRatio="Y"
            /></AFrame></P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">Click on <Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            fontDef="uicontrol">Yes</Font> to uninstall the previous version (recommended), or click
        on <Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="uicontrol">No</Font> to proceed
        without uninstalling the previous version.</P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">Choosing default options will create the following
        folder:</P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">
        <Font xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="codeph">C:\Program
            Files\Miramo\MiramoPDF 2.0.0</Font>
    </P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">The desktop shortcut will be updated to point to
        MiramoDesigner.exe in this folder, and the miramo.exe binary (composition engine) is located
        in the same folder.</P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">The PATH environment variable will be set as shown here. Note
        that if you chose not to uninstall the previous version, both the earlier version and 2.0.0
        install folders are included in the PATH environment variable, but the earlier version (1.6
        in the example shown) takes precedence.<AFrame xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            wrap="Y" position="runin" crop="N" startIndent="inherit" align="end"><Image
                file="screenshots/winpath.png" width="50mm" keepAspectRatio="Y"/></AFrame></P>
    <P paraDef="context" listLabel="N">If you wish to install multiple concurrent versions of the
        composition engine, and are publishing using the MiramoPDF DITA-OT plugin, the location of
        the miramo.exe binary may be configured using the <Font
            xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fontDef="codeph">miramopath</Font> ant build
        parameter.</P>
